<!-- Feature Highlights -->
<section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="section-container">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2>Powerful Features</h2>
            <p>Everything you need for visual programming in .NET</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-3">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">🖱️</div>
                <h3>Interactive Canvas</h3>
                <p>Pan, zoom, drag nodes, box-select, and create connections with mouse or touch. Full multi-touch support.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">⚡</div>
                <h3>Execution Engine</h3>
                <p>Run node graphs with parallel, sequential, or event-driven execution. Step-through debugging built in.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">🔌</div>
                <h3>Plugin System</h3>
                <p>Dynamically load custom node types from external assemblies with full lifecycle management.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">🏪</div>
                <h3>Plugin Marketplace</h3>
                <p>Browse, install, update, and manage plugins from local or remote repositories.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">🤖</div>
                <h3>AI Integration (MCP)</h3>
                <p>Model Context Protocol server enables Claude, Cursor, and other AI assistants to build graphs.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">🖥️</div>
                <h3>Headless Execution</h3>
                <p>Run node graphs programmatically without any UI — console apps, APIs, CI/CD pipelines.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">💾</div>
                <h3>Serialization</h3>
                <p>Save and load node graphs as JSON with version migration support.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">🎨</div>
                <h3>Custom Editors</h3>
                <p>9 built-in socket editors (text, number, bool, dropdown, slider, image) plus extensibility.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">📊</div>
                <h3>Variables &amp; Events</h3>
                <p>Graph-scoped variables with auto Get/Set nodes. Custom events with Trigger/Listener nodes.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">🔒</div>
                <h3>Type System</h3>
                <p>Type-safe socket connections with automatic type resolution and validation.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">🔍</div>
                <h3>Viewport Culling</h3>
                <p>Automatic performance optimization for large graphs — supports 500+ nodes smoothly.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="feature-icon">🧪</div>
                <h3>Well Tested</h3>
                <p>Comprehensive unit tests with bUnit + xUnit. 30+ test files covering every subsystem.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Screenshots -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="section-container">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2>See It in Action</h2>
            <p>The WebHost UI provides a full-featured visual programming environment</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-2">
            <div class="screenshot-card">
                <div class="screenshot-frame">
                    <img src="images/editor-events.png" alt="Event-driven nodes" />
                </div>
                <h4>Event System</h4>
                <p>Create event-driven flows with custom Trigger and Listener nodes</p>
            </div>
            <div class="screenshot-card">
                <div class="screenshot-frame">
                    <img src="images/editor-canvas.png" alt="Clean workspace" />
                </div>
                <h4>Clean Workspace</h4>
                <p>Variables, Events, and Properties panels alongside an intuitive canvas</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Architecture -->
<section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="section-container">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2>3-Tier Architecture</h2>
            <p>Clean separation of concerns for maximum flexibility</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-stack">
            <div class="arch-layer arch--core">
                <span class="arch-tag">Core</span>
                <h3>NodeEditor.Net</h3>
                <p>Pure .NET 10 class library — execution engine, models, ViewModels, registry, plugins, serialization, logging, and headless execution. No Blazor dependency.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-arrow">▲</div>
            <div class="arch-layer arch--ui">
                <span class="arch-tag">UI</span>
                <h3>NodeEditor.Blazor</h3>
                <p>Razor component library — canvas, nodes, editors, marketplace UI, and DI setup via <code>AddNodeEditor()</code>.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-arrow">▲</div>
            <div class="arch-layer arch--host">
                <span class="arch-tag">Host</span>
                <h3>NodeEditor.Blazor.WebHost</h3>
                <p>Blazor Server host — the runnable demo with MCP integration, graph presets, and plugin marketplace.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="section cta-section">
    <div class="section-container" style="text-align: center;">
        <h2>Ready to Build?</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 500px; margin: 12px auto 32px;">
            Get started with NodeEditor.Net in minutes. Clone the repo, add three lines of code, and you have a working visual editor.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
            <a href="getting-started" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Started Tutorial</a>
            <a href="documentation" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Browse Docs</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
